The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Fitness call in 6 weeks
                                                                                                                       7                                      Fitness call in 6 weeks
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: It is the tennis stars hand, which is in question. A dodgy wrist has worried Sania Mirza and the 2009 Australian Open mixed doubles champion, on Tuesday, revealed that she will need six weeks rest. The state of the injury then will determine her course of action.         
	On the horizon are the French Open in the last week of May, and the WTA events in Indian Wells and Miami. Ill not be hitting a ball for six weeks. After that the injury will have to assessed once more, Sania spelt out the recovery timeline at an event in the city. It is only then that Ill decide about returning to court.         
	The Hyderabad girl inaugurated a residential tennis academy, headed by former Davis Cupper Jaidip Mukerjea at Pailan, on the southern fringes of the city.         
	At a gathering where the crowd of VIPs and the chaos it generates threatened to take the focus away from tennis, Sania took and hit a few balls with dignitaries, including ministers Kshiti Goswami and Subodh Kant Sahay.         
	The inauguration over, Sania fielded some questions from the media. One of Indias Commonwealth Games medal hopes, she said she was looking forward to the event in Delhi.         
	Sachin Tendulkars name came up and Sania said she felt that the maestro should get the biggest prize of them all from the government.         
	Certainly, he (Sachin) deserves the Bharat Ratna. Of course, it is up to the government to decide, but, for me, Sachin definitely deserves it.                                                                                                                     
